## Code

- Stack: React, Vite, TypeScript, Vitest, react-router-dom, React Flow (`reactflow`).
- Study UI: [`src/components/StudyCard.tsx`](src/components/StudyCard.tsx) plus scoped styles in [`src/index.css`](src/index.css) (`study-*`, `study-anchor-panel`, `speak-button`). Follow [UX.md](UX.md) Study bullets on layout, contrast, cognate/caution rows, and interaction (including `prefers-reduced-motion`).
- Pure logic in `src/lib/` (e.g. progress, queue, anchor, **wordSearch**, **latinFold**, **crossLangLemmaAffinity**): extend or add **unit tests** when behavior changes.
- Topic rows and tags: [.cursor/rules/words-sky-topic-data.mdc](.cursor/rules/words-sky-topic-data.mdc) (`false-friend-XX-YY`, required full **`examples`**, optional `articles`). **A1 / CEFRLex-style** manual checks and **planned build-later tasks** are in that file (*A1 level checks*).
- Match existing patterns; keep changes scoped.

## Documentation

- When a change affects user-visible behavior, copy or flows, configuration, build/run steps, public APIs, or topic/agent conventions—update the **minimum** docs that would otherwise go stale.
- Prefer existing sources of truth: [UX.md](UX.md); [.cursor/rules/words-sky-topic-data.mdc](.cursor/rules/words-sky-topic-data.mdc); the relevant [.cursor/skills/](.cursor/skills/) `SKILL.md` when its conventions change; [README.md](README.md) only if install, dev, or build workflow changes.
- Do not add or expand markdown without a concrete stale-doc reason; if nothing needs updating, skip (note in summary if helpful).

## Before claiming a task done

Run `npm run test` and `npm run build` (and `npm run lint` when touching TS/TSX). Fix failures or say what is intentionally deferred. When applicable, include documentation updates per **Documentation** above.
